I‚Äôm not going to get into targeting, or the interception process, but hopefully the ‚Äúwe‚Äôll just shoot the missile down‚Äù folks understand why that‚Äôs not quite as easy as it sounds.

We could almost certainly shoot *one* missile down, but multiple is significantly harder. 11/X

If you‚Äôre thinking three minutes isn‚Äôt very much time to save millions of people, welcome to the dilemma of missile defense. 

This is before we even discuss things like missiles with decoys to spoof radar, multiple warheads, etc. 10/X

If we determine we *do* need to intercept the missile, we have about a 7 minute window in which that is a viable option. 

Inside that 7 minute window, there‚Äôs approximately a 3 minute ‚Äúsweet spot‚Äù that statistically affords the highest probability of a successful intercept. 9/X

During that 28 minutes, several things will happen quickly: 

- We‚Äôll detect a launch almost immediately 
- We‚Äôll plot the trajectory of the missile shortly after 
- We‚Äôll decide (based on trajectory) if it‚Äôs a threat that needs a kinetic response and/or interdiction 8/X
Using North Korea as an example, an ICBM would need roughly 28 minutes from launch in North Korea to impact in the United States. 7/X

US missile defense is good, but it‚Äôs not infallible. Folks seem to be under the impression that shooting a ballistic missile out of the sky is point-and-click, and that couldn‚Äôt be further from the truth. 6/X

Preemption requires a good intelligence picture, assets in the region, and a (potentially illegal) order for a first strike. 

Interdiction is much more clear-cut from a legal standpoint, but shooting a missile down is hard. 5/X

There are effectively two ways we can defend against intercontinental ballistic missiles (ICBMs): 

1. Preemption - AKA destroying or interfering with the missile(s) before they‚Äôre launched. 

2. Interdiction - intercepting the missile 4/X

Now, let‚Äôs talk missile defense.

A vast majority of what goes into missile defense is highly classified, so this is going to be a high-level overview. If you‚Äôre looking for US missile defense secrets, this is not the thread for you. 3/X
First, I have to say that I‚Äôm highly skeptical that Iran has any plans to try to turn New York into hellish ruins ‚Äî they‚Äôre a lot of things, but dumb isn‚Äôt one of them. 2/X

In light of Iranian social media threatening to build nukes and turn New York into ‚Äúhellish ruins,‚Äù I‚Äôve seen some *really* bad missile defense analysis. 

Naturally, that means it‚Äôs thread time. 1/X
